laboratory_examinations.findings: Interval placement of a right-sided PICC line noted; lung volumes slightly low but better expanded compared to the previous study. Less crowding of the pulmonary vasculature and improved bibasilar atelectasis. Stable cardiomediastinal contours. No pleural effusions or pneumothorax.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Lungs appear better expanded compared to the previous study.
